markets.title: Will any Israeli Cabinet member resign before May 2025?
markets.rules_primary: If any Minister of the Israeli Cabinet (including the Prime Minister) resigns before May 1, 2025, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: For the purpose of this market, the Israel Cabinet is defined as the following positions: Prime Minister, Deputy Prime Minister, Minister of Justice, Vice Prime Minister, Minister of the Interior, Minister of Health, Minister for the Development of the Negev and the Galilee and National Resilience, Minister of Diaspora Affairs, Minister for Social Equality, Minister for Women's Empowerment, Minister of Housing and Construction, Minister in the Prime Minister's Office, Minister of Agriculture and Rural Development, Minister of Aliyah and Integration, Minister of Communications, Minister of Culture and Sport, Minister of Defense, Minister of Finance, Minister in the Defense Ministry, Minister of the Economy, Minister of Education, Minister of Regional Cooperation, Minister in the Education Ministry, Minister of Environmental Protection, Minister of Foreign Affairs, Minister of Energy, Minister of Public Diplomacy, Minister of Intelligence, Minister of Heritage, Minister of Jerusalem Affairs and Jewish Tradition, Minister of Labor, Social Affairs, and Social Services, Minister in the Ministry of Labor, Social Affairs, and Social Services, Minister of Settlements and National Missions, Minister of National Security, Minister of Religious Affairs, Minister of Science and Technology, Minister of Strategic Affairs, Minister of Tourism, Minister of Transportation, Minister Without Portfolio in the Prime Minister's Office, Minister without portfolio. Deputy ministers do not count.
markets.early_close_condition: This market will close and expire early if the event occurs.
